  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler framework plugin extension points are defined in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository v1.32.0. All nine extension points are interface definitions located in pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go:\n\n1. **PreFilterPlugin** (line 512-531): Called at the beginning of the scheduling cycle to perform initial checks and optionally filter nodes. Executed via RunPreFilterPlugins() called from findNodesThatFitPod() in schedule_one.go:474.\n\n2. **FilterPlugin** (line 540-557): Called to filter out nodes that cannot run a pod. Executed via RunFilterPluginsWithNominatedPods() called from findNodesThatPassFilters() in schedule_one.go:629.\n\n3. **PostFilterPlugin** (line 561-581): Called when a pod cannot be scheduled to attempt making it schedulable via preemption. Executed via RunPostFilterPlugins() called from schedulingCycle() in schedule_one.go:175.\n\n4. **PreScorePlugin** (line 587-595): Informational plugin called after filtering phase with the list of feasible nodes. Executed via RunPreScorePlugins() called from prioritizeNodes() in schedule_one.go:778.\n\n5. **ScorePlugin** (line 607-616): Called to rank nodes that passed the filtering phase. Executed via RunScorePlugins() called from prioritizeNodes() in schedule_one.go:784.\n\n6. **ReservePlugin** (line 624-636): Called when the scheduler cache is updated. Executed via RunReservePluginsReserve() called from schedulingCycle() in schedule_one.go:208.\n\n7. **PreBindPlugin** (line 640-645): Called before binding a pod to a node. Executed via RunPreBindPlugins() called from bindingCycle() in schedule_one.go:296.\n\n8. **BindPlugin** (line 671-682): Called to bind a pod to a node. Executed via RunBindPlugins() called from bind() in schedule_one.go:978.\n\n9. **PostBindPlugin** (line 647-656): Called after a pod is successfully bound. Executed via RunPostBindPlugins() called from bindingCycle() in schedule_one.go:333.\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n- The Framework interface is defined in interface.go (lines 684-778) and implemented by frameworkImpl in pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go.\n\n- The frameworkImpl struct (line 52-90 in runtime/framework.go) maintains slices of each plugin type: preFilterPlugins, filterPlugins, postFilterPlugins, preScorePlugins, scorePlugins, reservePlugins, preBindPlugins, bindPlugins, postBindPlugins, and permitPlugins.\n\n- The getExtensionPoints() method in runtime/framework.go (line 103-118) defines the mapping between plugin configuration and plugin slices.\n\n- All built-in plugins are registered in pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go through the NewInTreeRegistry() function.\n\n- The complete scheduling cycle flow is orchestrated in pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go, starting with ScheduleOne() which calls schedulingCycle() and then bindingCycle(), invoking the extension points in the correct order.\n\n- Additional related interfaces include PreFilterExtensions (line 501-508 in interface.go), ScoreExtensions (line 598-603 in interface.go), and EnqueueExtensions (line 482-496 in interface.go) for optional plugin functionality."
}

